    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>A generic rect allocator. Given a set of rects and a target rect, finds the closest free rect next to the target (using dijkstra&apos;s algorithm). The class can be reused multiple times to avoid repeated heap allocation, it doesn&apos;t store any state other than memory pools. For optimal results you should bring your own AABB tree (see <computeroutput>FindPotentiallyOverlappingRects</computeroutput>) below, but in simple cases you can get away with a flat list. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
